<subSubSection id="C31E6567FFE7F6098BFD3DC5FBBBF4C6" pageId="35" pageNumber="93" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BBB36ECFFE7F6098BFD3DC5FB1CF5BA" blockId="35.[739,1333,2521,2948]" pageId="35" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="B970EAFEFFE7F6098BFD3DC5FCDAF661" bold="true" box="[739,895,2521,2554]" pageId="35" pageNumber="93">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C044D6FFFE7F6098A933DC5FCF9F5BA" authority="K. Andersen, 1908" authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1908" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Myonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="93" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leptodon">Myonycteris leptodon K. Andersen, 1908</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B6C3CB1FFE7F6098A733E18FB1CF5BA" box="[877,1209,2564,2593]" pageId="35" pageNumber="93">
“ 
<collectingCountry id="F313767CFFE7F6098A693E18FB94F5BA" box="[887,1073,2564,2593]" name="Sierra Leone" pageId="35" pageNumber="93">Sierra Leone</collectingCountry>
; Libera.”
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBB36ECFFE7F6098BFA3E34FBBBF4C6" blockId="35.[739,1333,2521,2948]" pageId="35" pageNumber="93">
Mpyonycteris 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D6FFFE7F6098A983E34FC4BF5D2" authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1908" box="[902,1006,2600,2633]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Myonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="93" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leptodon">leptodon</taxonomicName>
was considered a subspecies or synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D6FFFE7F6098D063E4FFB14F5EB" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1878" box="[1048,1201,2643,2672]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Myonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="93" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="torquata">M. torquata</taxonomicName>
. Analyses of cytochrome-b sequences in specimens from West Africa differed considerably (by 69 mutations) from M. ftorquata populations in Central Africa; therefore, the species name proposed by K. Andersen was reinstated. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
